  <evidence rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Use of Cookies Sci-News com uses cookie technology A cookie is a small amount of data which often includes a unique identifier that is sent to your computer or mobile phone browser from a websites computer and is stored on your devices hard drive A website can send its own cookie to your browser if your browsers preferences allow it but your browser only permits a website to access the cookies it has already sent to you not the cookies sent to you by other websites Many websites do this whenever a user visits their website in order to track online traffic flows</evidence>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

